org.anchoranalysis.feature.bean

Class Feature<T extends FeatureInput>

  • Object
    • AnchorBean<B>
      • InitializableBean<Feature<T>,FeatureInitialization>
        • Feature<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - input-type
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FeatureAllMemo, FeatureDoubleElem, FeatureEnergy, FeatureHistogram, FeatureListElem, FeatureMark, FeatureMarkCollection, FeatureObjectCollection, FeatureOperator, FeaturePairMemo, FeaturePairObjects, FeatureResults, FeatureSingleMemo, FeatureSingleObject, FeatureStack, FeatureUnary

    public abstract class Feature<T extends FeatureInput>
extends InitializableBean<Feature<T>,FeatureInitialization>
    Feature that calculates a result (double) for some parameters

    It should always be called in a context of a session, which first initializes the feature before doing calculations.

    Author:
    Owen Feehan

      • createListChildFeatures

        public final FeatureList<FeatureInput> createListChildFeatures()
                                                        throws BeanMisconfiguredException
        Returns a list of Features that exist as bean-properties of this feature, either directly or in lists.

        It does not recurse.

        It ignores features that are referenced from elsewhere.
